Full Description: Shiva.com is the resource for Jewish mourning. It provides an easy-to-use, efficient resource to help family members, friends, co-workers and acquaintances to honor the passing of loved ones. The site carefully blends centuries-old religious traditions with modern-day customs to help support, communicate and mourn. Shiva.com provides information along with guidance about appropriate items to send and words to express condolences in a respectable and understanding way. Shiva.com was designed with a wide range of users in mind understanding that visitors to the site come from different religious backgrounds and perspectives on faith. The site provides useful and reliable information that is easy to understand no matter what your religious perspective. It offers guidance for those seeking to understand Jewish mourning or access proper services to express and send condolences. Mourners, family, friends, colleagues and others can now learn, plan and send everything appropriate following the passing of a loved one. Anyone visiting shiva.com has access its vast resources, including the site’s Learning Center – where users can find a wealth of information during this most difficult time. Additionally, the Planning Center provides tools for organizing or supporting a shiva. Most notably, family, friends and co-workers now have a resource to Send appropriate sympathy items, including planting trees in Israel (through shiva.com’s partner, Jewish National Fund), traditional fruit baskets, baked goods and more to those in mourning via shiva.com directly or its Trusted Business Vendor Directory containing a comprehensive list of local Approved Providers.

Our objective is to protect capital and to generate compelling absolute returns over all market environments. On the long side, we focus primarily on senior and secured debt of lesser-followed, primarily middle-market U.S. high yield issuers, with particular expertise in distressed situations. On the short side, we seek fundamentally overvalued securities and economically deteriorating issuers, at times augmented by macro hedges to protect our portfolio. Our priority is to invest at the top of the capital structure, with a consistently high allocation to shorter duration, current-interest-paying securities. We believe that our investing strategy tends to result in low correlations to both the equity and credit markets, as well as low volatility. Our performance record, including predecessor firms, goes back over 23 years.

Full Description: Acris GmbH was founded 1998 as a spinoff of DPC Biermann GmbH, the German subsidiary of Diagnostic Products Corp., Los Angeles. Acris took over responsibility for marketing the DPC Biermann research products. From 1999 to 2003 Acris GmbH focused more and more on the research antibodies. In the beginning Acris GmbH served as a distributor for US and UK antibody manufacturers in the German market. In September 2003 Acris GmbH became a fully independent company and took over all research products and customers from DPC. Acris GmbH was renamed Acris Antibodies GmbH what should better reflect our business. From the very beginning it was Acris' mission to serve the research community with high quality research products. The idea was to resolve a problem that many researchers are confronted with: “How can I find a product/antibody which will work optimal in my research application”. To help these scientists Acris developed a platform for thousands of high quality antibodies in one easy to search online database. Since 2010, Acris has been able to offer more than 170,000 primary antibodies and more than 50,000 proteins, lysates and kits. Acris Antibodies developed from a German distributor to a global player in the research product / antibody market. Distributors in Europe and Asia were added and in the beginning of 2011 we opened a branch office in San Diego, USA. Since November 2012, Acris Antibodies GmbH is DIN EN ISO 9001 certified. We have implemented and certified our Quality Management to show our dedication towards our goal: We aim to satisfy our customers with outstanding service and high quality products. Learn more about our quality policy here. In the next couple of years Acris Antibodies will strengthen its international position and develop our database any further by adding new and innovative products like the Link-A-Light product line for quick and easy antibody or protein conjugation with dyes.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Community and Lifestyle, Manufacturing, Science and Engineering

It can be used for a consignment store or mall, art gallery, or used book store. We can help you track inventory, make sales, pay consignors, and keep employee information.  ConsignPro’s Software Solutions Our resale software holds the potential for a variety of applications. Whatever the use, its features are designed to keep your business running smoothly. Some of hundreds of great features include: •	Security Our log-in screen prevents unauthorized access to your POS system. Employees create a password, and you can assign them a permission level. This means that they have as much or as little access to the point-of-sale software as you decide. You can also track who is logging in and out of the system and when. We track any suspect behavior for you, reducing theft. •	POS Hardware We offer several packages with purchase of our software. These can include several easily integrated pieces of hardware. Scan guns, receipt printers, and cash drawers are designed to pair with the software you purchase. Our support team will help you install the hardware you buy from us. •	Customer Tracking Once your business is established, our software can even help it grow. Our customer tracking feature tracks consignors as well as customers. This means that you can tailor marketing campaigns to target your most loyal customers. We even offer a customer rewards feature that can give them a discount, if you choose. ConsignPro software has come highly recommended by all of our customers. Reviews on softwareadvice.com have rated us 4.9/5.0 in ease-of-use, functionality, quality, and customer support. ConsignPro considers all of its customers unpaid references, and invites prospective customers to contact them. ConsignPro provides the most for your money, ensuring a resale business’s success.
